params.name: isVisible
params.description: Specifies if the sheet is visible or not.

GetActiveCell.name: GetActiveCell
GetActiveCell.description: Returns an object that represents an active cell.

GetSelection.name: GetSelection
GetSelection.description: Returns an object that represents the selected range.

GetCells.name: GetCells
GetCells.description: Returns the ApiRange that represents all the cells on the worksheet (not just the cells that are currently in use).

params.name: row
params.description: The row number or the cell number (if only row is defined).

params.name: col
params.description: The column number.

GetRows.name: GetRows
GetRows.description: Returns the ApiRange object that represents all the cells on the rows range.

params.name: value
params.description: Specifies the rows range in the string or number format.

GetCols.name: GetCols
GetCols.description: Returns the ApiRange object that represents all the cells on the columns range.

params.name: sRange
params.description: Specifies the columns range in the string format.

GetUsedRange.name: GetUsedRange
GetUsedRange.description: Returns the ApiRange object that represents the used range on the specified worksheet.

SetName.name: SetName
SetName.description: Sets a name to the current active sheet.

params.name: sName
params.description: The name which will be displayed for the current sheet at the sheet tab.

GetRange.name: GetRange
GetRange.description: Returns an object that represents the selected range of the current sheet. Can be a single cell - A1, or cells from a single row - A1:E1, or cells from a single column - A1:A10, or cells from several rows and columns - A1:E10.

params.name: Range1
params.description: The range of cells from the current sheet.

params.name: Range2
params.description: The range of cells from the current sheet.

GetRangeByNumber.name: GetRangeByNumber
GetRangeByNumber.description: Returns an object that represents the selected range of the current sheet using the row/column coordinates for the cell selection.

params.name: nRow
params.description: The row number.

params.name: nCol
params.description: The column number.

FormatAsTable.name: FormatAsTable
FormatAsTable.description: Formats the selected range of cells from the current sheet as a table (with the first row formatted as a header). As the first row is always formatted as a table header, you need to select at least two rows for the table to be formed correctly.

params.name: sRange
params.description: The range of cells from the current sheet which will be formatted as a table.

SetColumnWidth.name: SetColumnWidth
SetColumnWidth.description: Sets the width of the specified column. One unit of column width is equal to the width of one character in the Normal style. For proportional fonts, the width of the character 0 (zero) is used.

params.name: nColumn
params.description: The number of the column to set the width to.

params.name: nWidth
params.description: The width of the column divided by 7 pixels.

params.name: bWithotPaddings
params.description: Specifies whether nWidth will be set without standard paddings.

SetRowHeight.name: SetRowHeight
SetRowHeight.description: Sets the height of the specified row measured in points. A point is 1/72 inch.

params.name: nRow
params.description: The number of the row to set the height to.

params.name: nHeight
params.description: The height of the row measured in points.

SetDisplayGridlines.name: SetDisplayGridlines
SetDisplayGridlines.description: Specifies whether the current sheet gridlines must be displayed or not.

params.name: isDisplayed
params.description: Specifies whether the current sheet gridlines must be displayed or not. The default value is true.

SetDisplayHeadings.name: SetDisplayHeadings
SetDisplayHeadings.description: Specifies whether the current sheet row/column headers must be displayed or not.

params.name: isDisplayed
params.description: Specifies whether the current sheet row/column headers must be displayed or not. The default value is true.

SetLeftMargin.name: SetLeftMargin
SetLeftMargin.description: Sets the left margin of the sheet.

params.name: nPoints
params.description: The left margin size measured in points.

GetLeftMargin.name: GetLeftMargin
GetLeftMargin.description: Returns the left margin of the sheet.

SetRightMargin.name: SetRightMargin
SetRightMargin.description: Sets the right margin of the sheet.

params.name: nPoints
params.description: The right margin size measured in points.

GetRightMargin.name: GetRightMargin
GetRightMargin.description: Returns the right margin of the sheet.

SetTopMargin.name: SetTopMargin
SetTopMargin.description: Sets the top margin of the sheet.

params.name: nPoints
params.description: The top margin size measured in points.

GetTopMargin.name: GetTopMargin
GetTopMargin.description: Returns the top margin of the sheet.

SetBottomMargin.name: SetBottomMargin
SetBottomMargin.description: Sets the bottom margin of the sheet.

params.name: nPoints
params.description: The bottom margin size measured in points.

GetBottomMargin.name: GetBottomMargin
GetBottomMargin.description: Returns the bottom margin of the sheet.

params.name: sPageOrientation
params.description: The page orientation type.

GetPrintHeadings.name: GetPrintHeadings
GetPrintHeadings.description: Returns the page PrintHeadings property which specifies whether the current sheet row/column headings must be printed or not.

SetPrintHeadings.name: SetPrintHeadings
SetPrintHeadings.description: Specifies whether the current sheet row/column headers must be printed or not.

params.name: bPrint
params.description: Specifies whether the current sheet row/column headers must be printed or not.

GetPrintGridlines.name: GetPrintGridlines
GetPrintGridlines.description: Returns the page PrintGridlines property which specifies whether the current sheet gridlines must be printed or not.

SetPrintGridlines.name: SetPrintGridlines
SetPrintGridlines.description: Specifies whether the current sheet gridlines must be printed or not.

params.name: bPrint
params.description: Defines if cell gridlines are printed on this page or not.

GetDefName.name: GetDefName
GetDefName.description: Returns the ApiName object by the worksheet name.

params.name: defName
params.description: The worksheet name.

AddDefName.name: AddDefName
AddDefName.description: Adds a new name to the current worksheet.

params.name: sName
params.description: The range name.

params.name: sRef
params.description: Must contain the sheet name, followed by sign ! and a range of cells. Example: "Sheet1!$A$1:$B$2".

params.name: isHidden
params.description: Defines if the range name is hidden or not.

GetComments.name: GetComments
GetComments.description: Returns all comments from the current worksheet.

SetHyperlink.name: SetHyperlink
SetHyperlink.description: Adds a hyperlink to the specified range.

params.name: sRange
params.description: The range where the hyperlink will be added to.

params.name: sAddress
params.description: The link address.

params.name: subAddress
params.description: The link subaddress to insert internal sheet hyperlinks.

params.name: sScreenTip
params.description: The screen tip text.

params.name: sTextToDisplay
params.description: The link text that will be displayed on the sheet.

AddChart.name: AddChart
AddChart.description: Creates a chart of the specified type from the selected data range of the current sheet. Please note that the horizontal and vertical offsets are calculated within the limits of the specified column and row cells only. If this value exceeds the cell width or height, another vertical/horizontal position will be set.

params.name: sDataRange
params.description: The selected cell range which will be used to get the data for the chart, formed specifically and including the sheet name.

params.name: bInRows
params.description: Specifies whether to take the data from the rows or from the columns. If true, the data from the rows will be used.

params.name: sType
params.description: The chart type used for the chart display.

params.name: nStyleIndex
params.description: The chart color style index (can be 1 - 48, as described in OOXML specification).

params.name: nExtX
params.description: The chart width in English measure units

params.name: nExtY
params.description: The chart height in English measure units.

params.name: nFromCol
params.description: The number of the column where the beginning of the chart will be placed.

params.name: nColOffset
params.description: The offset from the nFromCol column to the left part of the chart measured in English measure units.

params.name: nFromRow
params.description: The number of the row where the beginning of the chart will be placed.

params.name: nRowOffset
params.description: The offset from the nFromRow row to the upper part of the chart measured in English measure units.

AddShape.name: AddShape
AddShape.description: Adds a shape to the current sheet with the parameters specified. Please note that the horizontal and vertical offsets are calculated within the limits of the specified column and row cells only. If this value exceeds the cell width or height, another vertical/horizontal position will be set.

params.name: sType
params.description: The shape type which specifies the preset shape geometry.

params.name: nWidth
params.description: The shape width in English measure units.

params.name: nHeight
params.description: The shape height in English measure units.

params.name: oFill
params.description: The color or pattern used to fill the shape.

params.name: oStroke
params.description: The stroke used to create the element shadow.

params.name: nFromCol
params.description: The number of the column where the beginning of the shape will be placed.

params.name: nColOffset
params.description: The offset from the nFromCol column to the left part of the shape measured in English measure units.

params.name: nFromRow
params.description: The number of the row where the beginning of the shape will be placed.

params.name: nRowOffset
params.description: The offset from the nFromRow row to the upper part of the shape measured in English measure units.

AddImage.name: AddImage
AddImage.description: Adds an image to the current sheet with the parameters specified.

params.name: sImageSrc
params.description: The image source where the image to be inserted should be taken from (currently only internet URL or Base64 encoded images are supported).

params.name: nWidth
params.description: The image width in English measure units.

params.name: nHeight
params.description: The image height in English measure units.

params.name: nFromCol
params.description: The number of the column where the beginning of the image will be placed.

params.name: nColOffset
params.description: The offset from the nFromCol column to the left part of the image measured in English measure units.

params.name: nFromRow
params.description: The number of the row where the beginning of the image will be placed.

params.name: nRowOffset
params.description: The offset from the nFromRow row to the upper part of the image measured in English measure units.

AddWordArt.name: AddWordArt
AddWordArt.description: Adds a Text Art object to the current sheet with the parameters specified.

params.name: oTextPr
params.description: The text properties.

params.name: sText
params.description: The text for the Text Art object.

params.name: sTransform
params.description: Text transform type.

params.name: oFill
params.description: The color or pattern used to fill the Text Art object.

params.name: oStroke
params.description: The stroke used to create the Text Art object shadow.

params.name: nRotAngle
params.description: Rotation angle.

params.name: nWidth
params.description: The Text Art width measured in English measure units.

params.name: nHeight
params.description: The Text Art heigth measured in English measure units.

params.name: nFromCol
params.description: The column number where the beginning of the Text Art object will be placed.

params.name: nFromRow
params.description: The row number where the beginning of the Text Art object will be placed.

params.name: nColOffset
params.description: The offset from the nFromCol column to the left part of the Text Art object measured in English measure units.

params.name: nRowOffset
params.description: The offset from the nFromRow row to the upper part of the Text Art object measured in English measure units.

AddOleObject.name: AddOleObject
AddOleObject.description: Adds an OLE object to the current sheet with the parameters specified.

params.name: sImageSrc
params.description: The image source where the image to be inserted should be taken from (currently, only internet URL or Base64 encoded images are supported).

params.name: nWidth
params.description: The OLE object width in English measure units.

params.name: nHeight
params.description: The OLE object height in English measure units.

params.name: sData
params.description: The OLE object string data.

params.name: sAppId
params.description: The application ID associated with the current OLE object.

params.name: nFromCol
params.description: The number of the column where the beginning of the OLE object will be placed.

params.name: nColOffset
params.description: The offset from the nFromCol column to the left part of the OLE object measured in English measure units.

params.name: nFromRow
params.description: The number of the row where the beginning of the OLE object will be placed.

params.name: nRowOffset
params.description: The offset from the nFromRow row to the upper part of the OLE object measured in English measure units.

ReplaceCurrentImage.name: ReplaceCurrentImage
ReplaceCurrentImage.description: Replaces the current image with a new one.

params.name: sImageUrl
params.description: The image source where the image to be inserted should be taken from (currently only internet URL or Base64 encoded images are supported).

params.name: nWidth
params.description: The image width in English measure units.

params.name: nHeight
params.description: The image height in English measure units.

GetAllDrawings.name: GetAllDrawings
GetAllDrawings.description: Returns all drawings from the current sheet.

GetAllImages.name: GetAllImages
GetAllImages.description: Returns all images from the current sheet.

GetAllShapes.name: GetAllShapes
GetAllShapes.description: Returns all shapes from the current sheet.

GetAllCharts.name: GetAllCharts
GetAllCharts.description: Returns all charts from the current sheet.

GetAllOleObjects.name: GetAllOleObjects
GetAllOleObjects.description: Returns all OLE objects from the current sheet.

Move.name: Move
Move.description: Moves the current sheet to another location in the workbook.

params.name: before
params.description: The sheet before which the current sheet will be placed. You cannot specify "before" if you specify "after".

params.name: after
params.description: The sheet after which the current sheet will be placed. You cannot specify "after" if you specify "before".

GetFreezePanes.name: GetFreezePanes
GetFreezePanes.description: Returns the freeze panes from the current worksheet.

comment:
/**
	 * Class representing a sheet.
	 * @constructor
	 * @property {boolean} Visible - Returns or sets the state of sheet visibility.
	 * @property {number} Active - Makes the current sheet active.
	 * @property {ApiRange} ActiveCell - Returns an object that represents an active cell.
	 * @property {ApiRange} Selection - Returns an object that represents the selected range.
	 * @property {ApiRange} Cells - Returns ApiRange that represents all the cells on the worksheet (not just the cells that are currently in use).
	 * @property {ApiRange} Rows - Returns ApiRange that represents all the cells of the rows range.
	 * @property {ApiRange} Cols - Returns ApiRange that represents all the cells of the columns range.
	 * @property {ApiRange} UsedRange - Returns ApiRange that represents the used range on the specified worksheet.
	 * @property {string} Name - Returns or sets a name of the active sheet.
	 * @property {number} Index - Returns a sheet index.
	 * @property {number} LeftMargin - Returns or sets the size of the sheet left margin measured in points.
	 * @property {number} RightMargin - Returns or sets the size of the sheet right margin measured in points.
	 * @property {number} TopMargin - Returns or sets the size of the sheet top margin measured in points.
	 * @property {number} BottomMargin - Returns or sets the size of the sheet bottom margin measured in points.
	 * @property {PageOrientation} PageOrientation - Returns or sets the page orientation.
	 * @property {boolean} PrintHeadings - Returns or sets the page PrintHeadings property.
	 * @property {boolean} PrintGridlines - Returns or sets the page PrintGridlines property.
	 * @property {Array} Defnames - Returns an array of the ApiName objects.
	 * @property {Array} Comments - Returns all comments from the current worksheet.
	 * @property {ApiFreezePanes} FreezePanes - Returns the freeze panes for the current worksheet.
	 */

properties.name: Visible
properties.description: Returns or sets the state of sheet visibility.

properties.name: Active
properties.description: Makes the current sheet active.

properties.name: ActiveCell
properties.description: Returns an object that represents an active cell.

properties.name: Selection
properties.description: Returns an object that represents the selected range.

properties.name: Cells
properties.description: Returns ApiRange that represents all the cells on the worksheet (not just the cells that are currently in use).

properties.name: Rows
properties.description: Returns ApiRange that represents all the cells of the rows range.

properties.name: Cols
properties.description: Returns ApiRange that represents all the cells of the columns range.

properties.name: UsedRange
properties.description: Returns ApiRange that represents the used range on the specified worksheet.

properties.name: Name
properties.description: Returns or sets a name of the active sheet.

properties.name: Index
properties.description: Returns a sheet index.

properties.name: LeftMargin
properties.description: Returns or sets the size of the sheet left margin measured in points.

properties.name: RightMargin
properties.description: Returns or sets the size of the sheet right margin measured in points.

properties.name: TopMargin
properties.description: Returns or sets the size of the sheet top margin measured in points.

properties.name: BottomMargin
properties.description: Returns or sets the size of the sheet bottom margin measured in points.

properties.name: PageOrientation
properties.description: Returns or sets the page orientation.

properties.name: PrintHeadings
properties.description: Returns or sets the page PrintHeadings property.

properties.name: PrintGridlines
properties.description: Returns or sets the page PrintGridlines property.

properties.name: Defnames
properties.description: Returns an array of the ApiName objects.

properties.name: Comments
properties.description: Returns all comments from the current worksheet.

properties.name: FreezePanes
properties.description: Returns the freeze panes for the current worksheet.
